div2.p:
I saw no stragglers during the time I was with Pender's division; but although the Virginian army certainly does get over a deal of ground, yet they move at a slow dragging pace, and are evidently not good marchers naturally.
As Mr. Norris observedto me, Before this war we were a lazy set of devils;
our niggers worked for us, and none of us ever dreamt of walking, though we all rode a great deal.
